def standarize_plot_parameters():
    fig_width_pt = 448.13
    inches_per_pt = 1.0/72.27               # Convert pt to inches
    golden_mean = (np.sqrt(5)-1.0)/2.0         # Aesthetic ratio
    fig_width = fig_width_pt*inches_per_pt  # width in inches
    fig_height = fig_width*golden_mean       # height in inches
    params = {
        'axes.labelsize': 14,
        'legend.fontsize': 14,
        'xtick.labelsize': 12,
        'ytick.labelsize': 12,
        'figure.figsize': [fig_width, fig_height],
        'font.family': 'STIXGeneral',  # close enough to LaTeX font
        'font.size': 12,
        'figure.frameon': False
    }
    sn.set_style(params)

#method for truncating n to decimal places

from decimal import *

def truncate(f, n):
    '''Truncates/pads a float f to n decimal places without rounding'''
    s = '{:.4f}'.format(f)
    if 'e' in s or 'E' in s:
        return '{0:.{1}f}'.format(f, n)
    i, p, d = s.partition('.')
    if (i=='nan'):
        return Decimal(i)
    else:
        return Decimal('.'.join([i, (d)[:n]]))

#Method for calculating Radius Of Gyration. Needs a panda Dataframe as parameter
def calculate_rg(dataframe_in):
    
    rg_dict = {} #dictionary which will hold all the values. Keys will be the users, values the radius of gyration
    for user in set(dataframe_in.user.values):
        user_df = dataframe_in[dataframe_in['user']==user]

        user_trunc_lat_avg = user_df['lat'].mean() #Find the mean of all Latitude points
        user_trunc_lat_avg = truncate(user_trunc_lat_avg, 3) #truncate the latitude to 3 decimals
        user_trunc_lon_avg = user_df['lon'].mean() #Find the mean of all Longitude points
        user_trunc_lon_avg = truncate(user_trunc_lon_avg, 3) #truncate the longitude to 3 decimals

        r_cm = np.array([user_trunc_lat_avg, user_trunc_lon_avg]) #calculate the centre of mass

        total_sum = 0; # Σ
        ri_values =  pd.DataFrame(user_df.r_i.value_counts())

        N = ri_values.r_i.sum() #sum over all the r_i values

        #Equation 4.1
        for row in ri_values.itertuples():
            total_sum += math.pow(vincenty(np.array([row[0][0], row[0][1]]), r_cm).km,2) * row[1] # Σ

        r_g_user = math.sqrt(total_sum/N) #Divide by N and take the square root

        rg_dict[user] = r_g_user #save the value to the dictionary
        
    return rg_dict

        i=0

        for row in total_df.itertuples():
            lat_k += row[0][0]*row[1]

                avg_lat_2 = lat_k/total_avg_sum
                avg_lat_2 = truncate(avg_lat_2, 3)
                avg_lon_2 = lon_k/total_avg_sum

                avg_lat_10 = truncate(avg_lat_10, 3)
                avg_lon_10 = lon_k/total_avg_sum
                avg_lon_10 = truncate(avg_lon_10, 3)

            i+=1
            if(i>9):
                break

        r_cm_2 = np.array([avg_lat_2, avg_lon_2])
        r_cm_4 = np.array([avg_lat_4, avg_lon_4])

        r_cm_8 = np.array([avg_lat_8, avg_lon_8])
        r_cm_10 = np.array([avg_lat_10, avg_lon_10])

        #Equations 4.1, 4.2
        i=0
        for row in total_df.itertuples():
            total_sum += math.pow(vincenty(np.array([row[0][0], row[0][1]]), r_cm).km,2) * row[1] # Σ

            if (i<2):
                total_sum2 += math.pow(vincenty(np.array([row[0][0], row[0][1]]), r_cm_2).km,2) * row[1] # Σ k=2

            if (i<4):
                total_sum4 += math.pow(vincenty(np.array([row[0][0], row[0][1]]), r_cm_4).km,2) * row[1] # Σ k=4

            if (i<6):
                total_sum6 += math.pow(vincenty(np.array([row[0][0], row[0][1]]), r_cm_6).km,2) * row[1] # Σ k=6

            if (i<8):
                total_sum8 += math.pow(vincenty(np.array([row[0][0], row[0][1]]), r_cm_8).km,2) * row[1] # Σ k=8

            if (i<10):
                total_sum10 += math.pow(vincenty(np.array([row[0][0], row[0][1]]), r_cm_10).km,2) * row[1] # Σ k=10

            i+=1

        #Divide by N and take the square root
        r_g_user = math.sqrt(total_sum/N)
        r_g_user2 = math.sqrt(total_sum2/N_2)
        r_g_user4 = math.sqrt(total_sum4/N_4)
        r_g_user6 = math.sqrt(total_sum6/N_6)
        r_g_user8 = math.sqrt(total_sum8/N_8)
        r_g_user10 = math.sqrt(total_sum10/N_10)

        rg_dict[user] = r_g_user #rg
        rg_dict2[user] = r_g_user2 #2-rg
        rg_dict4[user] = r_g_user4 #4-rg
        rg_dict6[user] = r_g_user6 #6-rg
        rg_dict8[user] = r_g_user8 #8-rg
        rg_dict10[user] = r_g_user10 #10-rg
